data.name: radFromCurrent.HelpString
data.value: The EA Protocol Handler URL will be built with a connection string based on the connected repository. The information is encrypted but should not be considered secure. It is adviseable to use this where the connection string was configured with Integrated Security.

data.name: radUserDefined.HelpString
data.value: The EA Protocol Handler URL will be built for a EA repository as specified by the user. The value is usually a 'key' that the EA Protocol Handler may use to index a known set of EA repositories.

data.name: radDefault.HelpString
data.value: The EA Protocol Handler URL will be built for a fixed EA repository. This option only supports configurations where there is a single UML repository.

data.name: txtUserDefined.HelpString
data.value: A user defined value that the EA Protocol Handler is aware of.
